## Before Working

1. Read `docs/PLAYBOOK.md` — session entry point, identifies active lifecycle phase
2. If in execution phase: Read `docs/CURRENT_WORK.md` → `context/WORKING.md` → Phase SPEC.md
3. Sync: `git fetch origin && git log --oneline HEAD..origin/$(git branch --show-current) | head -5`

## TDD Gate (Non-Negotiable)

**No code without scenarios. No scenarios without acceptance criteria.**

| Step | Output | Gate |
|-|-|-|
| 1. Plan | SPEC.md + SCENARIOS.md | Planning outputs exist |
| 2. RED | Scenario runs and FAILS | Failure = correct (missing impl) |
| 3. GREEN | Implementation code, scenario PASSES | `{{ type_check_command }}` passes |
| 4. VALIDATE | `/verify:complete` passes | Hard block on missing scenarios |

**Scope classification:**

| Trigger (ANY match) | Scope | TDD Required? |
|-|-|-|
| New DB tables/columns | Standard+ | Yes |
| New API routes | Standard+ | Yes |
| New UI pages/major components | Standard+ | Yes |
| 4+ files modified | Standard+ | Yes |
| Single-file bug fix, no new surface area | Quick | No |

## Work Routing

| Source | Route |
|-|-|
| Quick fix (single-file, no new surface area) | Fix → Commit with `Fixes #N` |
| Standard+ (see TDD Gate scope triggers) | SPEC → SCENARIOS → RED → GREEN → VALIDATE |
| External concern | Append to `context/DISCOVERIES.md` → keep working |

## Before Writing Code

